# Conventional Commit format
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# Example: fix(core): resolve timeout handling in monitor thread
# Example (breaking): feat(cli)!: change default config file location
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, chore, ci, test, refactor, perf, security
# Scopes: cli, core, subprocess, docs, ci, deps
#
# Rules:
# - Use the imperative mood in the subject (e.g., "add", "fix", "update").
# - Lowercase the subject.
# - Keep subject concise and descriptive.
